Day 14: Jenkins

Jenkins is a CI/CD tool used to automate the software development process.
	• CI (Continuous Integration): Involves continuous build + continuous test. It merges old code with new code.
		○ Before CI: Work was manual and time-consuming.
		○ After CI: Everything is automated.
	• CD (Continuous Delivery): Deployment manually to prod environment.
	• CD (Continuous Deployment): Deployment automatically to prod environment.
	
Pipeline
A pipeline is a step-by-step process to execute a task.
	SOURCE CODE -> BUILD (convert from .java to .war) -> TEST -> DEPLOY

Environments
	1. DEV: Developers
	2. QA: Testers
	3. UAT: Client
		○ Note: The above are called Pre-Prod or Non-Prod.
	4. PROD: User (also called LIVE)

Jenkins Characteristics
	• Free and open source tool.
	• Platform independent.
	• Built on Java 11.
	• Port number for Jenkins is 8080.

Setup on EC2 Instance (Amazon Linux/RHEL)

	1. Spin up EC2 instance.
	2. sudo yum update -y
	3. Install Git, Java-1.8.0, and Maven:
		○ sudo yum install git java-1.8.0-openjdk maven -y
	4. Getting the Repo:
		○ Go to browser -> jenkins.io -> download -> under stable LTS -> select Red Hat Enterprise.
		○ Run these commands:
			§ sudo wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo
			§ sudo rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key
	5. Download Java-11 and Jenkins:
		○ sudo amazon-linux-extras install java-openjdk11 -y
		○ sudo yum install jenkins -y
		○ sudo update-alternatives --config java (Switch to the preferred version, which is 11 from the list).
		○ java -version -> To confirm the version in use.
	6. To Start Jenkins:
		○ sudo systemctl start jenkins.service
		○ sudo systemctl status jenkins.service

To Connect and Launch Jenkins

	1. Copy the Public IP from the EC2 instance.
		○ Format: Public-IP:8080
	2. Paste it in the browser (Sample: 35.180.225.237:8080).
	3. Go to Linux and type:
		○ sudo cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword
		○ A password will be generated.
	4. Copy the password from step 3 to authenticate in step 2.
	5. Wait for "Getting Started" to complete.
		○ Create Admin user account.
		○ Click on Save and Continue.

Integrate Git & Maven with Jenkins

A Simple CI/CD using Jenkins

	1. In your Jenkins dashboard, click on New Item.
	2. Enter Item Name: NETFLIX_CI_JOB.
	3. Select Free style project -> OK.
	4. Under GENERAL:
		○ Go to Source Code Management.
		○ Select Git.
		○ Paste the Netflix repository URL from Git: https://github.com/devopsbyraham/jenkins-java-project.git
		○ Branches Specifier: Confirm it is master (same as it is on Git).
	5. Go to Build Steps -> Add build step -> Execute shell.
		○ Type: mvn clean package
		○ (Note: This is the single command to build the source code).
	6. Click on Save.
	7. Click on Build Now.
		○ Check log below -> click on build history -> click on Console Output to see the BUILD SUCCESS.
	Note: In the console output, navigate to the path to see the .war file:
	/var/lib/jenkins/workspace/netflix/target/
